LORE midgaard-merchant
FLAGS MIDGAARD MERCHANT
- Guild Concordat stamp = minimum quality guarantee; unlicensed goods are
  cheaper and have no recourse mechanism
- Three founding trade blocs (River Factors, Upland Syndicate, Temple Compact)
  still shape pricing; their interests are not identical and sometimes
  contradict each other
- Tariff disputes go to the Magistrate Ledgerhouse; most are settled by
  a junior clerk before reaching a magistrate
- Upland ore quality varies by shipment; current shortage reported in
  Ash-and-Iron reserve stocks; prices elevated until northern routes clear
- Pilgrim trade at the Temple of the Resounding Heart brings seasonal revenue
  spikes; plan inventory accordingly around the memorial calendar
- The Lantern Registry posts official tariffs; discrepancies from posted rates
  are recoverable civil offenses; always get a receipt
~
